5. Environment Configuration and Secret Management

The FSI "Secure-by-Default" pillar mandates the complete decoupling of secrets from source control.

Required Runtime Environment Variables

The following exact keys must be used in the Google Secret Manager to ensure pipeline compatibility:

Variable	Required	Description	Source
APP_ENV	Yes	Defines environment (production/staging).	Cloud Run Env Var
FSI_PRODUCTION	Yes	Mandatory safety switch for validation.	Cloud Run Env Var
SECRET_KEY	Yes	Used for session signing.	Secret Manager (fsi-secret-key)
DATABASE_URL	Yes	SQLAlchemy connection string.	Secret Manager (fsi-database-url)

Strict Runtime Validation

When FSI_PRODUCTION is true, the application must perform a startup check on all critical variables. Any insecure configuration (e.g., missing secrets or default debug keys) must trigger an immediate application exit to prevent compromised runtimes.

All FSI applications mandate Python 3.10+. Use of Python 3.8 is permitted only for legacy maintenance and requires a technical exception from the Governance Lead.


