6. Communication Standards: Postmark Centralized Messaging

FSI mandates Postmark for all transactional email to ensure high deliverability and auditability for logistics workflows.

The Postmark-Only Mandate

1. Provider: MAIL_PROVIDER=postmark.
2. Enforcement: MAIL_ENFORCE_POSTMARK=true.
3. API Only: Use the Postmark API exclusively. SMTP is prohibited for new development.
4. Auditability: Every business unit must define a unique MAIL_MESSAGE_STREAM (e.g., MAIL_MESSAGE_STREAM=expenses).
5. Sender Identity: Standardize on MAIL_DEFAULT_SENDER=expense.reports@freightservices.net where applicable.

Service Layer Pattern

All email logic must reside in app/services/mail.py.

* Template Governance: Email bodies must never be hardcoded in Python.
* The Template Model Rule: Developers must use the template_model (Python dictionary) as the exclusive method for passing dynamic data to the Postmark API. Templates are managed within the Postmark UI to allow content updates without redeploying code.


