7. Frontend & Branding: Font-Loading and UI Consistency

Unified visual identity is critical for building internal trust. The FSI UI baseline utilizes a performance-optimized font strategy.

FSI Font-Loading Strategy

* Roboto: Standard for body copy and UI controls.
* Bebas Neue: Standard for display headings (.fsi-display).
* Optimization: Templates must include preconnect hints for fonts.googleapis.com and fonts.gstatic.com in the base.html header.
* Fallback Mandate: CSS must maintain the resilient stack: system-ui, sans-serif.

Privacy Trigger

Any application handling PII, sensitive logistics data, or governed by specific compliance regulations must transition from CDN-hosted to self-hosted fonts (stored in /static/fonts/) to prevent external infrastructure requests from client browsers.


