9. Development Lifecycle and Quality Assurance

Testing and Coverage Mandate

FSI-aligned repositories must maintain high test coverage.

* Command: pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing
* Requirement: Coverage reporting is a blocking requirement in all CI/CD pipelines.

Local Development Standard

1. Environment Parity: Mirror production using a local .env file derived from .env.example.
2. Runtime: Python 3.10+ is the standard.
3. Dependencies: Production builds must install only requirements.txt. Development tools are restricted to requirements-dev.txt.

Pre-Commit Checklist

Before any PR submission, engineers must verify:

* [ ] Every new database table is registered as a constant in models.py.
* [ ] Alembic migrations have been generated and validated locally.
* [ ] The full test suite passes with required coverage thresholds.
* [ ] Font-loading preconnect hints are present in base.html.
* [ ] No secrets (Postmark tokens, DATABASE_URL) are committed to source control.
* [ ] /readyz returns 503 with actionable guidance if schema is out of sync.
